==Old English==
===Etymology===
West Germanic, from Germanic ''*folijanan'', from Indo-European ''*(s)pol-, *(s)pal-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[fela|fēla]], Old Saxon [[gifolian|gifōlian]] (Dutch [[voelen]]), Old High German [[fuolen]] (German [[fühlen]]); and with Latin [[pollere]] ‘be strong, able’, Bulgarian [[палам]] ‘search’, Old Russian [[пальць]] (Russian [[палец]] ‘finger, toe’).

